1
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,498
- You all right, sir?
- Yes.

2
00:01:08,034 --> 00:01:09,695
So what are you doing here
at 4:00 in the morning?

3
00:01:09,769 --> 00:01:11,361
I'm a cop.

4
00:01:12,172 --> 00:01:15,903
- Got a badge?
- Was a cop, I'm leaving town.

5
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:20,911
I just thought I'd stand here
for a while till I went.

6
00:01:21,881 --> 00:01:23,508
That your car?

7
00:01:24,184 --> 00:01:27,210
-What division you work out of?
-Downtown, Homicide.

8
00:01:27,487 --> 00:01:29,455
- Who runs it?
- Captain Cronjager.

9
00:01:32,859 --> 00:01:34,588
I can smell booze on you.

10
00:01:38,064 --> 00:01:40,157
I'm waiting to sober up.

11
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:44,301
Want me to drive you home in 
your car?My partner can follow us.

12
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:49,833
I'll wait till I'm sober.

13
00:01:52,645 --> 00:01:54,272
Okay.

14
00:03:47,026 --> 00:03:48,118
Where you from?

15
00:03:52,532 --> 00:03:54,227
Where you headed?

16
00:03:58,538 --> 00:04:00,005
Massachusetts.

17
00:04:01,341 --> 00:04:02,831
Massachusetts?

18
00:04:03,509 --> 00:04:05,568
All the way to Massachusetts?

19
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:09,738
You gotta be kidding me, mister.
Massachusetts?

20
00:04:11,050 --> 00:04:14,076
<i>Paradise, Massachusetts is 
a long way from home.</i>

21
00:04:15,054 --> 00:04:17,352
But it's been my home for 20 years.

22
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:22,691
In many ways, this town and I
grew up together.

23
00:04:24,697 --> 00:04:28,690
I've appreciated the opportunity
to serve as your police chief

24
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:32,363
- and I tried never to forget...
- It's a sad day.

25
00:04:32,472 --> 00:04:36,238
...that the trust
you so generously placed in me

26
00:04:37,076 --> 00:04:38,065
had to be earned.

27
00:04:38,745 --> 00:04:39,905
Not once,

28
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:42,338
but every day.

29
00:04:42,649 --> 00:04:45,709
So, as I move on,

30
00:04:48,021 --> 00:04:49,921
I just want to say

31
00:04:51,057 --> 00:04:52,615
thank you.

32
00:04:54,093 --> 00:04:55,492
So...

33
00:04:55,862 --> 00:04:58,330
Before I start crying,
does anyone know a good joke?

34
00:04:59,699 --> 00:05:02,532
<i>So, this guy takes 
his old dog to the vet</i>

35
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,468
and he says, "Doc, it looks 
like it hurts when he pees. "

36
00:05:05,538 --> 00:05:07,028
Doc says, "How old is he?"

37
00:05:07,106 --> 00:05:11,770
Guy says, "Twelve. "
Doc says, "He's peed enough. "

38
00:05:13,346 --> 00:05:15,371
Not funny, huh?

39
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:45,937
Are you all right?

40
00:05:48,748 --> 00:05:50,409
Going far?

41
00:05:51,084 --> 00:05:52,483
Long way.

42
00:06:05,131 --> 00:06:07,190
I don't see why you feel 
the need to work.

43
00:06:07,266 --> 00:06:10,030
I like it. It gives me 
a sense of independence.

44
00:06:10,436 --> 00:06:12,802
Is that new police chief 
coming this week?

45
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,271
Yeah, from California.

46
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:16,806
That's a long away.

47
00:06:16,976 --> 00:06:18,841
Why is Lou retiring anyway?

48
00:06:19,245 --> 00:06:21,941
He's a relatively young man.

49
00:06:22,815 --> 00:06:24,339
I don't know.
He said he's fed up with the job.

50
00:06:24,417 --> 00:06:25,850
He's put his 20 years in.

51
00:06:27,153 --> 00:06:28,677
Don't you have to be at the bank?

52
00:06:29,088 --> 00:06:30,783
I can go to work when I want.

53
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:36,025
That'll look good on you.

54
00:06:37,196 --> 00:06:38,254
Why don't you come back to bed?

55
00:06:38,831 --> 00:06:41,231
I can't. I'm going to be late.

56
00:06:41,601 --> 00:06:42,795
Sorry.

57
00:07:11,998 --> 00:07:15,399
I've always wanted to drive 
across country.Take the back roads.

58
00:07:15,868 --> 00:07:17,460
I got nothing better to do.

59
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:19,437
<i>What if you don't get the job?</i>

60
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:23,165
<i>Where are you?</i>

61
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:25,968
Missouri, I think.

62
00:07:26,512 --> 00:07:27,877
<i>What's that noise?</i>

63
00:07:28,181 --> 00:07:29,478
I'm in a phone booth.

64
00:07:29,549 --> 00:07:32,245
The phone in my room doesn't work.
It's raining.

65
00:07:32,685 --> 00:07:34,050
<i>You drinking?</i>

66
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,246
Yes.

67
00:07:35,488 --> 00:07:38,048
<i>You need to be 
carefuI of that.</i>

68
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:39,216
I know.

69
00:07:39,992 --> 00:07:41,892
<i>Am I losing you, Jesse?</i>

70
00:07:43,029 --> 00:07:45,429
There's some danger of it, Jenn.

71
00:08:17,563 --> 00:08:19,258
Tequila Sunrise.

72
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:23,395
Hi.

73
00:08:26,072 --> 00:08:27,334
Hi.

74
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:37,506
You come here often?

75
00:08:37,984 --> 00:08:39,474
What's your sign?

76
00:08:39,819 --> 00:08:41,377
Is there a hidden camera in here?

77
00:08:41,954 --> 00:08:43,854
Gee, I was sure that would work.

78
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:46,515
My name's Sandy.

79
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:49,319
- And you are?
- Jesse.

80
00:08:49,829 --> 00:08:52,855
I'm a student here.
I don't figure you for one.

81
00:08:52,965 --> 00:08:54,762
Grad student.

82
00:08:57,003 --> 00:08:59,130
Okay. I'm not in school.

83
00:09:00,106 --> 00:09:03,473
-What do you do for a living,Jesse?
-I'm an insurance adjuster.

84
00:09:03,643 --> 00:09:06,771
So, are you working on a case or 
you have a thing for college girls?

85
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:08,905
- Both.
- I'm one.

86
00:09:09,081 --> 00:09:12,016
- A case or college girl?
- Both.

87
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,712
And what do you do, Sandy?

88
00:09:15,821 --> 00:09:17,618
I already told you, 
I'm a student.

89
00:09:19,992 --> 00:09:22,017
You're kind of old for me.

90
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,998
Everybody says that.

91
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,560
You want to go someplace?

92
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:32,464
That's a very nice offer, Sandy,

93
00:09:33,706 --> 00:09:35,970
but I'm already going someplace.

94
00:09:38,311 --> 00:09:39,712
I admire your spirit. 
You know, just...

95
00:09:41,347 --> 00:09:45,283
Take all the back roads,
get in the car and just drive.

96
00:09:45,351 --> 00:09:47,114
I mean, I think it's great.

97
00:09:49,522 --> 00:09:50,853
Fifty grand.

98
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:52,288
Lou.

99
00:09:53,225 --> 00:09:54,658
It's the end of it.

100
00:09:56,529 --> 00:09:58,588
Hasty, is there any other way?

101
00:09:58,664 --> 00:10:01,394
No, there's no other way. Listen, 
I just can't afford you anymore.

102
00:10:02,301 --> 00:10:05,532
- We already picked your replacement so...
- You're just gonna have to pay him.

103
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:07,832
No, why would I?
The guy's pathetic, he's a loser.

104
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:11,103
He's just looking for a nice quiet place
to hide, and I'm gonna give it to him.

105
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:12,676
Yeah, well, he just might not be
the answer to that...

106
00:10:12,745 --> 00:10:15,077
You know what? It's not your 
problem. Don't worry about it.

107
00:10:15,147 --> 00:10:18,139
Just forget about us, 
forget about this town.

108
00:10:20,486 --> 00:10:21,544
Hey.

109
00:10:25,491 --> 00:10:26,549
Gonna miss you.

110
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:30,062
Go find what's at the end 
of that rainbow, all right?

111
00:11:02,461 --> 00:11:03,985
<i>What time is it there?</i>

112
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:05,820
10:45.

113
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,299
<i>It's 7.;45 here.</i>

114
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:10,460
That would be my guess.

115
00:11:10,770 --> 00:11:13,295
<i>-What are you wearing tomorrow?
-I don't know.</i>

116
00:11:13,372 --> 00:11:16,068
<i>Wear your blue suit.
You look so handsome in it.</i>

117
00:11:17,309 --> 00:11:19,539
<i>I wasn't telling you, Jesse.</i>

118
00:11:20,246 --> 00:11:22,646
<i>I'm thinking about 
going into therapy.</i>

119
00:11:22,882 --> 00:11:24,315
Well, do me a favor, Jenn.

120
00:11:24,383 --> 00:11:26,351
If you see a shrink, 
see a real shrink.

121
00:11:26,752 --> 00:11:30,483
Not some idiot who reads your 
aura and does crystal therapy.

122
00:11:30,623 --> 00:11:34,389
<i>I'm just so mixed up about things.
My career, and you, and me...</i>

123
00:11:34,493 --> 00:11:35,892
And Elliott.

124
00:11:36,996 --> 00:11:39,123
<i>I don't want to talk to you
when you're like this!</i>

125
00:11:43,736 --> 00:11:47,103
<i>I made a mistake, but I don't see
why I should be singled out for it.</i>

126
00:11:47,173 --> 00:11:49,573
<i>Everyone's goofed 
off around here.</i>

127
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:52,509
<i>The Caine's a slack ship.The men 
act like a pack of cutthroats,</i>

128
00:11:52,578 --> 00:11:54,443
<i>the decks look like
 a Singapore junk.</i>

129
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:58,477
<i>I take it, then, that you must 
also strongly disapprove of leave.</i>

130
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:00,314
<i>Go ahead, Keith, 
man to man.</i>

131
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:02,217
<i>Sir, I'm in no position
to approve or disapprove.</i>

132
00:12:03,089 --> 00:12:06,286
<i>I only know that my conception of
a captain seems different from your own.</i>

133
00:12:06,959 --> 00:12:09,519
<i>I'll take it 
under advisement.</i>

134
00:12:09,595 --> 00:12:11,392
<i>Since you feeI so bitter,</i>

135
00:12:11,831 --> 00:12:14,925
<i>perhaps what's in the dispatch
will brighten your day.</i>

136
00:12:17,536 --> 00:12:21,073
<i>As you can see, Keith,
I'm being relieved of command.</i>

137
00:13:10,689 --> 00:13:12,281
What are you looking at?

138
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:08,377
You're welcome.

139
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:11,376
Obviously, you know,
we think your resume is impressive

140
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:12,781
or you wouldn't be sitting here.

141
00:14:12,852 --> 00:14:15,252
So this interview is 
basically a formality.

142
00:14:15,387 --> 00:14:19,915
But I am head of town council,
so I guess it's my job to ask.

143
00:14:20,893 --> 00:14:23,453
We talked to your Captain...

144
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:26,221
- Cronjager.
- Cronjager.

145
00:14:26,732 --> 00:14:28,723
And he speaks well of you, but...

146
00:14:28,801 --> 00:14:31,235
He fired me for being 
drunk on the job.

147
00:14:36,075 --> 00:14:37,599
He said he thought it might 
have something to do

148
00:14:37,676 --> 00:14:38,938
with problems in your marriage.

149
00:14:39,245 --> 00:14:42,271
I guess I did go off the deep end 
for a bit, but I'm fine now.

150
00:14:42,414 --> 00:14:44,678
So, it wasn't an ongoing thing,
you just went through a rough patch

151
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:47,241
in your marriage and you needed 
a drink. I've been there myself.

152
00:14:47,353 --> 00:14:50,083
You know, when a man like you with your
record applies for a job like this...

153
00:14:50,322 --> 00:14:52,790
I just think you had a few 
too many drinks, I mean...

154
00:14:52,858 --> 00:14:55,656
Most of us would have done the same 
thing under the circumstances.

155
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,423
I don't have a problem 
here, do you, Lou?

156
00:14:57,596 --> 00:14:59,120
No problem, Hasty.

157
00:15:02,368 --> 00:15:04,427
You make sure you give 
these to the kids.

158
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:06,500
I'm gonna miss you, Lou.

159
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:09,630
What's the new guy like?

160
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:11,766
He seemed nice,

161
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,971
-except he smelled like a brewery.
-You're kidding me.

162
00:15:15,047 --> 00:15:16,139
Hi!

163
00:15:16,215 --> 00:15:19,343
Hey, Jesse, this is Molly Crane.

164
00:15:19,818 --> 00:15:21,911
Molly, this is Jesse Stone, 
your new chief.

165
00:15:22,021 --> 00:15:24,114
- Nice to meet you, Molly.
- And you.

166
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:26,653
This is Boomer.

167
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:30,619
Well, I was just packing up 
a few things. I'll...

168
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,628
Don't let me run you out.

169
00:15:32,698 --> 00:15:34,689
As a matter of fact,
I'd like to talk to you if I could.

170
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:37,967
Sure. Please.

171
00:15:50,382 --> 00:15:51,940
Weird sitting here.

172
00:15:52,651 --> 00:15:54,482
Is this a first-name department?

173
00:15:54,753 --> 00:15:56,584
- Has been.
- Good.

174
00:15:57,523 --> 00:16:00,492
- How you feel about retiring?
- Relieved.

175
00:16:00,559 --> 00:16:03,153
- You didn't like being chief?
- Not really.

176
00:16:03,329 --> 00:16:04,956
Pay's not worth the aggravation.

177
00:16:05,331 --> 00:16:06,889
Tell me about the aggravation.

178
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:09,726
You, you're used to 
a big force, big city.

179
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:12,600
Here, you're an employee 
of the town.

180
00:16:12,738 --> 00:16:15,673
And sometimes the 
town and the police

181
00:16:15,741 --> 00:16:18,505
don't exactly agree
on how things should get done.

182
00:16:18,577 --> 00:16:20,704
That's exactly what I'm used to.

183
00:16:22,281 --> 00:16:23,543
So, what're you going to do?

184
00:16:24,616 --> 00:16:27,551
I was going to throw the fishing rod
in the back of the car and drive.

185
00:16:27,619 --> 00:16:29,211
Never did that before.

186
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:30,550
Always wanted to.

187
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:33,454
Mr. Stone, it's your new boss.

188
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:35,823
Just press the lighted button.

189
00:16:44,703 --> 00:16:46,102
Change your mind?

190
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:49,663
<i>Listen, Jesse, we're having a little
fundraiser at our yacht club Saturday.</i>

191
00:16:49,775 --> 00:16:51,538
<i>I think you should be there.</i>

192
00:16:51,610 --> 00:16:53,908
<i>- I will be.
- Good.</i>

193
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:00,208
Well, good luck.

194
00:17:00,953 --> 00:17:02,545
Thank you, Lou.

195
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:28,980
Here's Lou Carson's badge and gun.
They belong to the department.

196
00:17:29,148 --> 00:17:32,049
Thanks, but I got my own gun.
I will need a permit.

197
00:17:32,117 --> 00:17:33,345
Yes, you will.

198
00:17:33,452 --> 00:17:35,317
And I guess I'll need 
some business cards.

199
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:36,979
Well, I think you 
should get some.

200
00:17:42,094 --> 00:17:44,688
What exactly do you do, Molly?

201
00:17:44,763 --> 00:17:46,321
I'm a police officer.

202
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,559
Actually, most of the time,
I'm the dispatcher.

203
00:17:48,634 --> 00:17:49,726
Who do you dispatch?

204
00:17:49,802 --> 00:17:53,568
-Usually one of two people, small town.
-You know a good realtor?

205
00:17:53,639 --> 00:17:57,575
I know who my boss would recommend.
I think I got a card someplace.

206
00:18:16,161 --> 00:18:19,927
Officer Simpson just called. They have
a domestic dispute out on Sylvan Road.

207
00:18:19,998 --> 00:18:21,363
I think you should be there.

208
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:23,157
Okay.

209
00:18:26,238 --> 00:18:28,229
You know where Sylvan Road is?

210
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:31,933
No.

211
00:18:34,046 --> 00:18:35,604
Thank you.

212
00:18:37,683 --> 00:18:41,642
I don't think I smell like 
a brewery. I was drinking Scotch.

213
00:19:07,246 --> 00:19:08,975
- Jesse Stone.
- Luther Simpson.

214
00:19:09,047 --> 00:19:10,344
Walk with me.

215
00:19:11,183 --> 00:19:12,377
Carole Genest called us.

216
00:19:12,451 --> 00:19:15,147
Said her ex-husband forced his way
into the house, threatened her.

217
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:17,415
- Who's the kid?
- Their daughter.

218
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:20,688
He's pretty belligerent. D'Angelo's 
up there  trying to calm him down.

219
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:22,453
Don't let her come in.

220
00:19:26,031 --> 00:19:28,761
Why don't you give me the 
divorce? What do you want?

221
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:30,461
- You want money?
- You got money.

222
00:19:30,636 --> 00:19:33,161
- So what! So what!
- Anthony D'Angelo. How are you doing?

223
00:19:33,739 --> 00:19:36,674
- Any more kids in the house?
- There's a couple of kids upstairs.

224
00:19:36,742 --> 00:19:38,175
- Who are you?
- You got kids, Anthony?

225
00:19:38,577 --> 00:19:40,067
Yeah, I got three.

226
00:19:40,245 --> 00:19:43,043
-Do what you can to make them feel safe.
-Okay.

227
00:19:43,115 --> 00:19:45,083
Hey, buddy, I said, who are you?

228
00:19:50,722 --> 00:19:52,553
I'm the new police chief, sir.

229
00:19:53,659 --> 00:19:56,184
Oh, yeah. I heard about you.

230
00:19:56,261 --> 00:19:58,161
Only good things, I hope.

231
00:19:58,263 --> 00:19:59,730
Oh, you're a funny guy.

232
00:20:00,832 --> 00:20:03,824
Does Mrs. Genest have
a restraining order on you, sir?

233
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:04,960
Yeah, so?

234
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,902
He's gonna kill me one day, 
the bastard.

235
00:20:06,972 --> 00:20:09,372
-Did he say he was going to kill you?
-Every time I see him.

236
00:20:09,441 --> 00:20:12,899
-Can you people do anything about him?
-Yes, ma'am, we can.

237
00:20:12,978 --> 00:20:15,970
Did he hit you or 
in any way assault you?

238
00:20:16,148 --> 00:20:17,410
No, not this time.

239
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,782
She's okay.

240
00:20:23,855 --> 00:20:24,981
Did he force his way in?

241
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:29,118
Yeah, yeah, I tried to lock the 
door, but he's still got a key.

242
00:20:29,261 --> 00:20:31,695
- It's my house.
- Has he assaulted you in the past?

243
00:20:31,763 --> 00:20:34,254
Sure, he's beat the crap out of me
a lot of times.

244
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,460
Well, we probably don't have
an assault charge here.

245
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:39,367
We may get forced entry
even though he had a key.

246
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:43,101
But obviously, we've got him for
violating the restraining order.

247
00:20:43,175 --> 00:20:45,643
Restraining order don't mean crap,
and you know it.

248
00:20:46,211 --> 00:20:47,508
Yes, sir, I know.

249
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:51,414
I just go to court with my lawyer,
they issue a new restraining order.

250
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:53,244
I am out of there in 20 minutes.

251
00:20:53,318 --> 00:20:55,650
That's the way it usually works,
especially if you've got some money.

252
00:20:55,721 --> 00:20:57,120
Which I do.

253
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,887
So...

254
00:21:00,192 --> 00:21:04,288
I guess that means I get to come 
in here and visit my wife

255
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,493
just as much as I please.

256
00:21:09,568 --> 00:21:11,058
Is that true?

257
00:21:13,538 --> 00:21:15,005
You just said there's nothing 
you can do about it.

258
00:21:15,073 --> 00:21:19,032
No, sir, I said the restraining 
order probably wouldn't work.

259
00:21:19,511 --> 00:21:20,944
Isn't that the same thing?

260
00:21:21,513 --> 00:21:22,741
Not really.

261
00:21:32,658 --> 00:21:34,387
If you come near 
this woman again,

262
00:21:34,726 --> 00:21:38,526
if anything happens to her, 
or her kids,no matter what,

263
00:21:38,764 --> 00:21:40,527
no matter whose fault it is,

264
00:21:40,599 --> 00:21:44,501
I will kick you around this town
until you look like road kill.

265
00:21:46,171 --> 00:21:49,163
And if you're annoying, 
like you were today,

266
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:52,436
I just might shoot you.

267
00:21:55,113 --> 00:21:58,082
Stay here with D'Angelo
until Mr. Genest leaves.

268
00:21:58,350 --> 00:21:59,977
What if he comes back?

269
00:22:00,285 --> 00:22:02,810
I don't think he'll come back.

270
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:13,658
Molly, can I get a cup of coffee?

271
00:22:13,965 --> 00:22:15,626
If you make it.

272
00:22:15,701 --> 00:22:19,262
Just because I'm the dispatcher
doesn't mean I can't do police work.

273
00:22:27,346 --> 00:22:29,337
We need to talk.

274
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:35,517
I should have introduced myself earlier.
I'm Abby Taylor, the city attorney.

275
00:22:35,587 --> 00:22:36,611
Jesse Stone.

276
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:39,088
- May I call you Jesse?
- Of course, Abby.

277
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:45,425
Whatever the circumstances
of your police work in Los Angeles,

278
00:22:45,797 --> 00:22:48,789
this is a town where everyone's
civil liberties are important.

279
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:52,200
Now, I can certainly sympathize
with Carole Genest's situation,

280
00:22:52,304 --> 00:22:54,636
but you cannot go around
beating people up.

281
00:22:55,006 --> 00:22:57,133
- Can I ask you a question?
- Of course.

282
00:22:57,442 --> 00:23:01,003
You asked if you could call me Jesse.
I said you could, but you didn't.

283
00:23:01,646 --> 00:23:03,807
- Excuse me?
- You didn't use my name.

284
00:23:04,249 --> 00:23:07,275
What does that have to do
with you assaulting Mr. Genest?

285
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:08,917
Just seemed odd to me.

286
00:23:10,689 --> 00:23:14,352
Do you have anything to say on the matter 
of your assault on Mr. Genest?

287
00:23:14,626 --> 00:23:18,255
The restraining order wasn't working.
Think of me as implementing it.

288
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:21,532
You really need to take 
this more seriously.

289
00:23:25,370 --> 00:23:29,204
You really need to take
this more seriously, Jesse.

290
00:23:30,108 --> 00:23:33,441
You really need to take
this more seriously, Jesse.

291
00:23:33,512 --> 00:23:35,036
No, I don't, Abby.

292
00:23:35,113 --> 00:23:37,104
You don't make it easy, Jesse.

293
00:23:37,182 --> 00:23:40,049
Joe Genest should be kicked
in the gonads once a day.

294
00:23:40,218 --> 00:23:42,584
It was necessary to 
get his attention.

295
00:23:42,654 --> 00:23:45,350
The town council is prepared
to go forward from here,

296
00:23:45,690 --> 00:23:46,884
but they would like your assurance

297
00:23:46,958 --> 00:23:49,188
that something like this
will not occur in the future.

298
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:52,196
- It might.
- You don't give an inch, do you?

299
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:53,695
Jesse.

300
00:23:54,132 --> 00:23:55,258
Jesse.

301
00:23:57,335 --> 00:24:00,270
Have you had much experience
with people like Mr. Genest?

302
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:03,875
People in South Central L.A.
would keep Joe Genest for a pet.

303
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:05,409
Are you married, Abby?

304
00:24:06,611 --> 00:24:07,839
No.

305
00:24:07,946 --> 00:24:10,710
I don't see what that has to do
with the issue before us.

306
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:12,079
Me, either.

307
00:24:12,317 --> 00:24:13,511
Have you ever been married?

308
00:24:13,585 --> 00:24:15,382
- Yes.
- But you're not married now?

309
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:16,478
No.

310
00:24:16,555 --> 00:24:17,749
- Divorced?
- Yes.

311
00:24:19,257 --> 00:24:22,886
Jesse, one of the rules of conversation
is that when asked a question,

312
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:24,861
you don't give a one-word answer.

313
00:24:24,930 --> 00:24:27,922
Okay, want to have dinner with me?

314
00:24:29,835 --> 00:24:31,325
Yes.

315
00:24:42,214 --> 00:24:43,306
It's good.

316
00:24:44,015 --> 00:24:45,505
Holster your weapon.

317
00:24:46,718 --> 00:24:47,878
You might want to 
get into the habit

318
00:24:47,953 --> 00:24:50,012
of keeping your finger
outside the trigger guard.

319
00:24:50,555 --> 00:24:51,613
If you're handling a suspect,

320
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:54,352
you might get a sympathetic 
response and shoot somebody.

321
00:24:54,793 --> 00:24:58,194
And you don't just stand there,
you shoot and move.

322
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:07,065
How'd you learn 
to shoot like that?

323
00:25:07,572 --> 00:25:08,834
Practice.

324
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:18,615
So, in a fight, front sight.

325
00:25:21,052 --> 00:25:24,112
You hear I was drunk 
at my job interview?

326
00:25:24,723 --> 00:25:26,520
I did hear something about that.

327
00:25:26,691 --> 00:25:27,851
- Small town.
- Small town.

328
00:25:30,529 --> 00:25:33,862
I wouldn't have 
hired me, would you?

329
00:25:34,499 --> 00:25:37,627
Well, I don't know.

330
00:25:38,970 --> 00:25:41,871
Any idea why Lou Carson retired?

331
00:25:42,607 --> 00:25:44,131
I don't know.

332
00:25:47,279 --> 00:25:50,146
<i>Hello, you've reached Paradise 
Realty. Please leave a message.</i>

333
00:25:51,249 --> 00:25:54,377
My name's Jesse Stone. I'm 
calling about finding a residence.

334
00:25:54,486 --> 00:25:57,512
You can reach me at the 
police station. Thank you.

335
00:25:58,890 --> 00:26:00,380
<i>- I'll start with an egg.
- All righty.</i>

336
00:26:00,458 --> 00:26:02,483
<i>One egg. Now, you don't
have to use eggs.</i>

337
00:27:23,341 --> 00:27:24,899
Paradise Police Station.

338
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:28,008
- Hey, Molly.
- Hey, Lou. Where are you?

339
00:27:28,146 --> 00:27:29,477
I don't know.

340
00:27:30,181 --> 00:27:31,739
Doesn't really matter.

341
00:27:32,350 --> 00:27:34,682
This just doesn't 
make any sense.

342
00:27:35,854 --> 00:27:38,823
Maybe you'll be 
surprised about Stone.

343
00:27:39,724 --> 00:27:42,022
He's got more iron in him
than I was expecting.

344
00:27:42,093 --> 00:27:43,560
Yeah, maybe I won't.

345
00:27:43,628 --> 00:27:45,755
Boy, does this guy have baggage.

346
00:27:49,067 --> 00:27:52,594
Listen, Molly, there's 
something I want you to know.

347
00:27:53,872 --> 00:27:55,897
<i>I always enjoyed 
working with you.</i>

348
00:27:57,509 --> 00:27:59,534
And I consider you my friend.

349
00:28:00,645 --> 00:28:02,135
Thanks, Lou.

350
00:28:02,547 --> 00:28:03,946
<i>Keep in touch.</i>

351
00:28:04,916 --> 00:28:06,713
Bye, Molly.

352
00:28:30,875 --> 00:28:31,864
What are you doing?

353
00:29:24,996 --> 00:29:26,930
I don't think he'll 
do that again.

354
00:29:27,732 --> 00:29:29,427
Maybe not if you're around.

355
00:29:30,135 --> 00:29:32,160
He hasn't bothered 
me since that day.

356
00:29:34,205 --> 00:29:36,264
How long are you going to
stick around here for?

357
00:29:37,575 --> 00:29:38,906
I don't know.

358
00:29:42,447 --> 00:29:45,746
I'm worried about Michelle. 
She's older...

359
00:29:45,817 --> 00:29:48,684
- How old is she?
- Fifteen.

360
00:29:48,753 --> 00:29:50,243
- Tough age.
- Yeah.

361
00:29:51,322 --> 00:29:53,187
She took the divorce really hard.

362
00:29:53,925 --> 00:29:56,951
- She hates her dad.
- That's too bad.

363
00:29:57,095 --> 00:29:59,757
- You think so?
- Fathers are important.

364
00:30:01,599 --> 00:30:03,965
- You want some more coffee?
- Yes, thank you.

365
00:30:07,005 --> 00:30:09,405
- Luther?
- Yes, ma'am.

366
00:30:11,242 --> 00:30:13,210
You get the house as 
part of the divorce?

367
00:30:13,278 --> 00:30:15,143
Yeah, yeah.

368
00:30:16,014 --> 00:30:18,039
He's supposed to pay me alimony,
but he never does.

369
00:30:18,116 --> 00:30:19,845
Must be tough to keep 
the payments up.

370
00:30:19,951 --> 00:30:20,940
Well, I...

371
00:30:21,252 --> 00:30:24,346
You know,I got to pay taxes quarterly,
but at least there's no mortgage.

372
00:30:24,422 --> 00:30:26,083
- Well, that's good.
- Yeah.

373
00:30:26,157 --> 00:30:28,682
Joe bought it for cash 
when we got married.

374
00:30:31,930 --> 00:30:33,227
What's he do?

375
00:30:36,668 --> 00:30:40,764
He works in Boston.
He never shared his work with me.

376
00:30:41,339 --> 00:30:45,207
My ex-husband has 
a very bad temper.

377
00:30:46,110 --> 00:30:48,578
I learned very early 
not to question him.

378
00:30:50,215 --> 00:30:53,651
Besides, I'm not very smart.

379
00:30:54,419 --> 00:30:57,820
I never learned anything in 
school. I didn't even graduate.

380
00:30:58,156 --> 00:31:00,420
Taking care of me was 
his job, right?

381
00:31:01,626 --> 00:31:03,321
Well, I'll talk to him.

382
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:07,020
You know, you're going
to need to be careful.

383
00:31:07,632 --> 00:31:10,931
Joe's mean. He's gonna 
wanna get even.

384
00:31:12,203 --> 00:31:13,727
Joe's a fake.

385
00:31:14,205 --> 00:31:18,335
Sometimes for a minute he knows it
and he knows that I know it, too.

386
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:20,902
He isn't really tough.

387
00:31:21,379 --> 00:31:22,846
And you are?

388
00:31:23,848 --> 00:31:25,475
Yes, ma'am. I am.

389
00:31:28,987 --> 00:31:31,888
I find dealing with cash
unbelievably tedious.

390
00:31:31,956 --> 00:31:33,548
Yeah, but you're 
pretty good at that.

391
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:36,458
Started as a teller, 
worked my way up.

392
00:31:39,864 --> 00:31:43,197
I hear you had a little run-in
with our new chief.

393
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:46,203
Yeah, the son of 
a bitch blindsided me.

394
00:31:46,571 --> 00:31:50,530
I hope your little personal and petty
problems with him don't get in our way.

395
00:31:50,608 --> 00:31:52,337
He's the chief of police.

396
00:31:53,811 --> 00:31:55,039
So what?

397
00:31:55,213 --> 00:31:59,377
I get $1,114,905.
 You wanna do a recount?

398
00:31:59,450 --> 00:32:00,815
I'll take your count.

399
00:32:00,885 --> 00:32:04,343
Okay, well, then, your share
of my eight percent...

400
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:07,424
$22,298.

401
00:32:08,026 --> 00:32:10,153
Oh, that's the wrong 
number, Hasty.

402
00:32:10,795 --> 00:32:12,558
We're equal partners now.

403
00:32:13,665 --> 00:32:15,155
Well, Joe, I don't 
want to diminish

404
00:32:15,233 --> 00:32:17,360
your very valuable contribution
to this little enterprise,

405
00:32:17,435 --> 00:32:18,902
but there's no way in hell
you're getting half...

406
00:32:19,003 --> 00:32:20,766
Lou Carson's dead.

407
00:32:24,075 --> 00:32:25,235
What?

408
00:32:25,343 --> 00:32:27,868
He had a terrible accident.

409
00:32:34,218 --> 00:32:36,550
What an incredibly 
stupid thing to do.

410
00:32:37,121 --> 00:32:39,851
Don't worry, they're 
never gonna find him.

411
00:32:40,258 --> 00:32:43,091
He knew everything.
Come on, he was a danger to us.

412
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:48,020
- He never would have said a word.
- What difference does it make?

413
00:32:48,099 --> 00:32:49,327
He's dead.

414
00:32:51,336 --> 00:32:53,327
That makes you an accessory.

415
00:32:54,272 --> 00:32:55,296
So...

416
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:57,206
From now on

417
00:32:58,476 --> 00:32:59,807
I get half.

418
00:33:01,512 --> 00:33:02,672
Thanks.

419
00:33:04,015 --> 00:33:06,745
I wouldn't have figured you
for a beer drinker.

420
00:33:07,385 --> 00:33:09,910
I'm not. I'm a Scotch 
on the rocks drinker.

421
00:33:10,588 --> 00:33:13,352
Just didn't want to get drunk
on our first date.

422
00:33:13,624 --> 00:33:15,091
Do you get drunk?

423
00:33:15,326 --> 00:33:17,817
I have trouble stopping 
when I start.

424
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:21,994
Is that what happened 
on the job interview?

425
00:33:23,201 --> 00:33:25,669
Actually, I had way too much 
the night before.

426
00:33:25,737 --> 00:33:29,400
I just made the mistake of having 
one in the morning to steady up.

427
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:34,672
Well, he hired you anyway, so 
he must have seen something in you.

428
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:38,380
- Maybe.
- Why maybe?

429
00:33:38,950 --> 00:33:40,884
I wouldn't have hired me.

430
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:44,921
What's your take on our boss?

431
00:33:45,490 --> 00:33:49,756
My father told me to never trust 
a man that smiles all the time.

432
00:33:49,827 --> 00:33:51,294
That's good advice.

433
00:33:52,296 --> 00:33:54,696
If you want a Scotch, go ahead.

434
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,158
I'm willing to risk 
it if you are.

435
00:34:01,939 --> 00:34:04,464
Did your ex-wife ever remarry?

436
00:34:04,542 --> 00:34:07,102
No, but she's in another 
guy's bed a lot.

437
00:34:07,345 --> 00:34:09,210
And that hurts.

438
00:34:12,283 --> 00:34:15,013
Maybe it would help 
if you got even.

439
00:34:22,393 --> 00:34:25,760
I think coffee and donuts
tend to certify one's copness.

440
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:27,263
Thanks for buying.

441
00:34:27,932 --> 00:34:30,298
I'm trying to prove 
I'm a regular guy.

442
00:34:32,470 --> 00:34:34,062
Luther your real name?

443
00:34:34,138 --> 00:34:37,505
My mother teaches Sunday school.
She's a very religious person.

444
00:34:37,575 --> 00:34:39,907
Named me after 
some religious guy.

445
00:34:39,977 --> 00:34:42,036
Gym teacher called me Spider
when I was in the fourth grade

446
00:34:42,113 --> 00:34:43,705
and that stuck for a while.

447
00:34:43,781 --> 00:34:47,842
- I don't see you as a Spider.
- Well, what do you see me as?

448
00:34:48,252 --> 00:34:50,049
Stop the car, Suitcase.

449
00:34:50,121 --> 00:34:51,713
- What did you say?
- Stop the car.

450
00:34:51,789 --> 00:34:53,279
No, after that.

451
00:35:03,534 --> 00:35:06,128
Drive around the block a couple 
of times, Suitcase.

452
00:35:19,884 --> 00:35:21,784
You gonna run me out 
of here or what?

453
00:35:21,853 --> 00:35:22,911
No.

454
00:35:23,087 --> 00:35:26,614
You come here, you smoke dope.
I chase you out, you come back.

455
00:35:26,691 --> 00:35:28,386
It's a waste of my time and yours.

456
00:35:28,826 --> 00:35:31,852
-You gonna kick me in the nuts?
-That would be difficult.

457
00:35:34,999 --> 00:35:36,364
You know,

458
00:35:37,368 --> 00:35:40,531
-you can't prove I'm smoking dope.
-Doesn't matter.

459
00:35:40,605 --> 00:35:42,232
So, why don't you just
leave me alone, then?

460
00:35:42,306 --> 00:35:45,139
-Why don't you go to school?
-School sucks.

461
00:35:55,019 --> 00:35:57,487
So, I guess you just think it's 
okay to push me around?

462
00:35:57,555 --> 00:36:00,456
-Am I pushing you around, Michelle?
-How do you know my name?

463
00:36:00,525 --> 00:36:02,925
I'm the police chief, 
I know everything.

464
00:36:06,464 --> 00:36:08,955
You know, I saw you going
into the Gray Gull last night.

465
00:36:09,834 --> 00:36:11,301
Small town.

466
00:36:11,836 --> 00:36:14,066
Aren't you a little old for her?

467
00:36:14,572 --> 00:36:17,700
I don't know. Maybe I'll ask her.

468
00:36:17,942 --> 00:36:19,637
Did you have a drink?

469
00:36:20,444 --> 00:36:22,105
Yes, I did.

470
00:36:22,246 --> 00:36:24,476
So how come that's okay
and smoking dope isn't?

471
00:36:24,549 --> 00:36:27,575
It's legal, and smoking 
dope is illegal.

472
00:36:27,652 --> 00:36:30,951
- So that makes it right?
- Nope, just legal and illegal.

473
00:36:31,556 --> 00:36:34,491
- Well, that sucks.
- A lot of things suck.

474
00:36:35,459 --> 00:36:40,226
You said stuff was just legal or illegal.
Well,what about it being right or wrong?

475
00:36:40,298 --> 00:36:44,064
I'm not in the right and wrong business.
I'm in the legal and illegal business.

476
00:36:44,135 --> 00:36:47,104
- You just don't want to answer.
- No, I don't mind answering.

477
00:36:47,572 --> 00:36:50,097
Actually, that was 
part of my answer.

478
00:36:50,741 --> 00:36:53,335
You and I both know that 
sitting around here all day

479
00:36:53,411 --> 00:36:55,936
smoking dope isn't the right thing
to do with your life.

480
00:36:56,013 --> 00:36:58,311
Who the hell are you
to say what's right for me?

481
00:36:58,583 --> 00:37:00,050
The guy you asked.

482
00:37:06,057 --> 00:37:09,686
Most people don't have trouble 
seeing what's right and wrong.

483
00:37:09,927 --> 00:37:12,418
Doing it is sometimes complicated,

484
00:37:12,496 --> 00:37:15,226
but knowing what's right
usually isn't so hard.

485
00:37:16,200 --> 00:37:19,692
And chasing you out of here
is obviously not the right way

486
00:37:19,971 --> 00:37:21,939
to help you do the right thing.

487
00:37:22,173 --> 00:37:26,303
- So, why are you still here?
- Trying to do the right thing.

488
00:37:37,054 --> 00:37:38,578
It has a living area.

489
00:37:38,656 --> 00:37:41,625
It has a kitchen with a dining 
area and a half bath.

490
00:37:41,692 --> 00:37:43,683
- Mrs. Hathaway...
