01:17:41,790 --> 01:17:45,191
Sorry to bother you in the middle
of the night, but you said anytime.

983
01:17:45,260 --> 01:17:47,854
<i>Listen, something's come up.
We have to talk.</i>

984
01:17:47,929 --> 01:17:50,124
- What's going on?
- Can it wait till morning?

985
01:17:50,198 --> 01:17:52,132
- If you say so, boss.
- What's going on?

986
01:17:52,200 --> 01:17:53,997
Right. I'll call you first 
thing in the morning.

987
01:17:54,069 --> 01:17:55,058
<i>Fine.</i>

988
01:18:35,310 --> 01:18:37,471
The son of a bitch has landed.

989
01:18:41,917 --> 01:18:45,318
-I thought you were gonna call me.
-Well, you said it was urgent.

990
01:18:45,387 --> 01:18:47,412
I'm sorry, boss, you said anytime.

991
01:18:47,489 --> 01:18:49,320
- What's going on?
- Want some coffee?

992
01:18:49,391 --> 01:18:51,416
Coffee? No, I don't want coffee.

993
01:18:55,430 --> 01:18:57,261
Lou Carson was murdered.

994
01:18:58,400 --> 01:18:59,924
Murdered?

995
01:19:01,303 --> 01:19:03,897
Well, I find that 
hard to believe.

996
01:19:04,239 --> 01:19:07,333
You know what? I actually...
I will have some coffee.

997
01:19:09,611 --> 01:19:12,512
Molly, can we have another 
cup of coffee?

998
01:19:12,814 --> 01:19:14,907
- You told me it was a car accident.
- I was wrong.

999
01:19:14,983 --> 01:19:17,918
-Newspapers called it a car accident.
-That's what the police gave them.

1000
01:19:17,986 --> 01:19:20,853
-But you remember this guy Joe Genest?
-Joe Genest?

1001
01:19:23,391 --> 01:19:25,859
Molly, close the door.

1002
01:19:28,296 --> 01:19:31,129
- You think Joe Genest killed Lou?
- I know it.

1003
01:19:31,199 --> 01:19:34,100
- How do you know it?
- I can't tell you.

1004
01:19:36,204 --> 01:19:39,264
Look, Hasty,
I know I owe you a lot but this...

1005
01:19:42,744 --> 01:19:45,542
All right. All right.

1006
01:19:46,148 --> 01:19:48,173
But this has to stay between us.

1007
01:19:48,316 --> 01:19:49,874
Yeah, of course, I understand.

1008
01:19:49,951 --> 01:19:52,852
Well, Healey found evidence
that Joe was at the scene.

1009
01:19:53,121 --> 01:19:55,851
Oh, he found it. Why hasn't
 he arrested him, then?

1010
01:19:55,924 --> 01:19:59,325
Well,they don't have enough to make
a case.They don't have a motive yet but...

1011
01:19:59,394 --> 01:20:02,522
See, I think I do. J
oe works for the mob.

1012
01:20:02,597 --> 01:20:05,998
And I think he and Lou had some 
kind of deal that went bad.

1013
01:20:08,270 --> 01:20:09,999
There's something else.

1014
01:20:12,174 --> 01:20:14,404
Joe's sleeping with your wife.

1015
01:20:17,746 --> 01:20:21,182
I think if he's arrested, 
it's gonna come out.

1016
01:20:24,286 --> 01:20:26,379
No one else knows about this.

1017
01:20:28,089 --> 01:20:31,684
I appreciate that you came
to me first with this.

1018
01:20:31,760 --> 01:20:34,456
I'm sorry to be the one 
to have to tell you.

1019
01:20:37,399 --> 01:20:40,129
- I'll walk you out.
- Yeah.

1020
01:21:39,494 --> 01:21:40,756
I got it.

1021
01:21:46,334 --> 01:21:48,802
- Hello.
- Jesse, this is Hasty. Listen.

1022
01:21:48,870 --> 01:21:51,930
This thing has really thrown me 
for a loop,and I need to talk.

1023
01:21:52,007 --> 01:21:54,202
I understand. I'll come 
to you, boss.

1024
01:21:54,276 --> 01:21:56,267
No, no. It's got to be 
somewhere private.

1025
01:21:56,344 --> 01:21:58,608
I don't want everybody 
to know about this.

1026
01:21:58,680 --> 01:22:00,944
<i>You know where that 
rusted ship is tied up?</i>

1027
01:22:01,016 --> 01:22:03,075
- Yes.
- Tonight, 8:00.

1028
01:22:03,184 --> 01:22:05,584
- I'll be there.
- Good. Thanks.

1029
01:22:11,326 --> 01:22:13,294
He'll be there.

1030
01:22:13,962 --> 01:22:16,954
You got to talk to him in private
about what?

1031
01:22:20,302 --> 01:22:23,169
Anything you want to say
to me there, Hasty?

1032
01:22:24,839 --> 01:22:29,105
I don't think there is anything I could 
say that'll make a difference,will it?

1033
01:23:33,341 --> 01:23:35,673
I work for the mob and I kill people.

1034
01:23:35,744 --> 01:23:37,041
Excuse me?

1035
01:23:37,712 --> 01:23:40,237
You asked what I do for a living.

1036
01:23:41,850 --> 01:23:43,784
Give me your gun.

1037
01:23:44,452 --> 01:23:45,783
No.

1038
01:23:47,822 --> 01:23:50,188
Put your hands behind your head.

1039
01:23:50,258 --> 01:23:51,555
No.

1040
01:23:52,327 --> 01:23:53,419
Excuse me?

1041
01:23:54,262 --> 01:23:57,629
I'm not putting my hands behind
 my head. I'm drinking coffee.

1042
01:23:58,233 --> 01:24:00,030
And you're gonna 
shoot me anyway.

1043
01:24:00,101 --> 01:24:02,126
That's a good point.

1044
01:24:17,786 --> 01:24:19,583
Is he dead?

1045
01:24:19,654 --> 01:24:20,678
Yeah.

1046
01:24:20,755 --> 01:24:22,188
How do you know?

1047
01:24:23,525 --> 01:24:24,787
You just know.

1048
01:24:31,499 --> 01:24:35,663
Tragically, Joe's ambitions
exceeded his abilities.

1049
01:24:36,037 --> 01:24:38,733
And it's one way
to keep him away from my wife.

1050
01:24:39,674 --> 01:24:41,369
You all right?

1051
01:24:41,743 --> 01:24:43,574
Too soon to tell.

1052
01:24:51,286 --> 01:24:52,617
Oh, Hasty.

1053
01:24:53,855 --> 01:24:55,220
Yeah, I know.

1054
01:24:56,091 --> 01:24:59,720
I was growing really fond of you,too.
I'm sorry to put you through this.

1055
01:24:59,794 --> 01:25:02,319
This? This is nothing.

1056
01:25:02,530 --> 01:25:04,589
I just had to bury my dog.

1057
01:25:05,767 --> 01:25:08,258
What'd you do, Hasty? 
See this in a movie?

1058
01:25:08,536 --> 01:25:12,063
You shoot Joe with the Chief's gun.
And then you use his on me.

1059
01:25:12,707 --> 01:25:14,038
Pretty much.

1060
01:25:14,109 --> 01:25:19,513
Well, the problem is you might have trouble
explaining why Joe was shot in the back.

1061
01:25:24,052 --> 01:25:25,144
Oh, right.

1062
01:25:25,253 --> 01:25:27,983
You're out of your league, Hasty.
Don't do this.

1063
01:25:28,923 --> 01:25:30,914
I don't wanna see you get hurt.

1064
01:25:31,993 --> 01:25:33,722
I'm the one with the gun.

1065
01:25:33,895 --> 01:25:35,362
Not the only one.

1066
01:25:35,964 --> 01:25:37,795
Don't move a muscle, Hasty.

1067
01:25:44,205 --> 01:25:46,867
Oh, hell. No.

1068
01:25:48,743 --> 01:25:50,301
Just put it down.

1069
01:25:53,548 --> 01:25:54,981
<i>Did you get all that, Molly?</i>

1070
01:25:55,049 --> 01:25:57,711
Tell the son of a bitch we got it all.

1071
01:26:05,260 --> 01:26:07,694
There's another one in his pocket.

1072
01:26:11,966 --> 01:26:13,729
I was ready, Jesse.

1073
01:26:14,269 --> 01:26:16,237
Sure you were, Suitcase.

1074
01:26:36,191 --> 01:26:37,783
Good God.

1075
01:26:44,599 --> 01:26:46,999
You should've done 
something to stop it.

